The AmaZulu Royal Household has lashed out at the media over reports there are divisions within the family. Courtesy #DStv403 KWANONGOMA - The AmaZulu Royal Household has lashed out at the media over reports there are divisions within the family. The late King Goodwill Zwelithini's sister, Princess Thembi Ndlovu has rejected rumours that she and her brother, Prince Mbonisi Zulu are implicated in the poisoning of the late Queen Mantfombi Dlamini, over the succession of the next monarch. READ: KZN government requests state funeral for AmaZulu Regent Princess Ndlovu also says they are not excluding AmaZulu Traditional Prime Minister, Chief Mangosuthu Buthelezi from royal matters. This comes after Buthelezi claimed that some family members were holding secret meetings. The princess claims that at times it is difficult to reach common ground with the Prime Minister.